---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import TrustBlock from "../components/TrustBlock.astro";
import FoundingCTA from "../components/FoundingCTA.astro";
import PricingBadge from "../components/PricingBadge.astro";

const title = "Rescue a Failing Software Project | Ascend Griffin";
const description =
  "Rescue a failing software project — vibe-coded apps, vendor ghosting, technical debt spirals. Buyer-side ally stops the bleeding. From $2,500/month retainer.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="svc">
    {/* ── Hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-hero">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">01</div>
          <div class="rail-label">Rescue</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-hero-body">
          <p class="svc-epigraph">
            "By the time a founder calls for a rescue,<br />
            it's never the bug that's bleeding the budget."
          </p>

          <h1 class="svc-h1">
            Rescue a failing software project — <em>stop the bleeding</em>, on your side.
          </h1>

          <p class="svc-lede">
            Project burning budget. Vendor ghosting. Velocity gone. Technical debt eating every sprint. Before you fire the team, rebuild from scratch, or write off the spend — a structured rescue from someone whose only interest is your outcome.
          </p>

          <PricingBadge price="from $2,500" duration="monthly retainer" unit="/month" />

          <div class="svc-hero-cta">
            <a
              href="#book"
              class="svc-btn-primary"
              data-modal="booking"
              data-subject="support"
              data-source="rescue-hero"
            >
              Request rescue call →
            </a>
            <a href="#scenarios" class="svc-btn-ghost">See how it works →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <TrustBlock />

    {/* ── Scenarios ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section" id="scenarios">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">02</div>
          <div class="rail-label">Three rescue scenarios</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">Three patterns I read most often.</h2>
          <p class="svc-section-lede">
            Each starts looking like a different problem and ends looking like the same one: someone needs to be in the room reading the situation honestly.
          </p>

          <article class="icp-card">
            <header class="icp-header">
              <span class="icp-num">A</span>
              <h3 class="icp-title">The vendor is ghosting you.</h3>
            </header>
            <p>Calls reschedule. Updates stop. The Slack channel where work used to happen has been quiet for three weeks. Maybe they're overloaded; maybe they've decided your project isn't profitable; maybe their senior dev quit and they're hoping you don't notice. Either way — you can't reach them and the burn keeps running. <em>First job: figure out whether to fix the relationship or end it cleanly.</em></p>
            <hr class="hairline" />
          </article>

          <article class="icp-card">
            <header class="icp-header">
              <span class="icp-num">B</span>
              <h3 class="icp-title">Scope creep spiral.</h3>
            </header>
            <p>Started at $40K. Now at $80K with the original feature list still half-shipped. Every change request lands on Friday with a new "this will need another two weeks." You're not sure whether you're being taken for a ride or whether the original quote was just dishonestly low. <em>First job: separate the legit re-scopes from the padding, and re-paper the engagement before another month bleeds.</em></p>
            <hr class="hairline" />
          </article>

          <article class="icp-card">
            <header class="icp-header">
              <span class="icp-num">C</span>
              <h3 class="icp-title">The team isn't delivering — and you can't tell why.</h3>
            </header>
            <p>People are working. Standups happen. Sprint reviews show movement. But shipping has stalled, your gut says something's wrong, and nobody on the team is the one to say it. <em>First job: read the situation from outside the politics — process, people, scope, or stack — and surface the actual blocker without burning bridges.</em></p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Rescue arc ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section svc-section-muted">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">03</div>
          <div class="rail-label">The rescue arc</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">Three phases. Each one ends with a decision you can make.</h2>

          <ol class="ledger">
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">01</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>Diagnostic (week 1-2).</h4>
                <p>Read the codebase, the contract, the comms history, and the team. Identify what's actually broken vs. what's symptomatic. End-of-phase artifact: a one-page rescue plan you can show co-founders or board.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">02</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>Stabilize (weeks 3-8).</h4>
                <p>Re-paper the vendor relationship or end it. Restore weekly delivery cadence. Triage the technical debt — what to fix, what to live with, what to plan around. By end of this phase: predictable shipping has resumed and the immediate financial bleed has stopped.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">03</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>Hand-off (week 8+).</h4>
                <p>Either: the project is stable with the existing team and I step out, leaving documentation behind. Or: we transition to a vetted vendor from my network with a structured handover. Either path ends with the project running without me in the room.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Not included ──────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">04</div>
          <div class="rail-label">What this is not</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">What a rescue <em>isn't</em>.</h2>

          <ul class="exclude">
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>Engineering management replacement.</strong> I read; I don't run your engineers daily. If you need a fractional eng manager, that's a different hire.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>A code refactor.</strong> I don't rewrite. I tell you what needs rewriting and by whom.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>"Just fire the vendor."</strong> Sometimes that's the answer. Often the cheaper move is fixing the relationship — and you need someone independent to call which is which.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>A guaranteed save.</strong> Some projects shouldn't be rescued. Honest answer is part of the value.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <FoundingCTA service="rescue" spotsLeft={2} />
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <script
    type="application/ld+json"
    set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      name: "Project Rescue",
      provider: {
        "@type": "Person",
        name: "Taras Smaliukh",
        url: "https://ascendgriffin.org/about/",
      },
      areaServed: ["Ukraine", "United Kingdom", "Germany", "United States"],
      description,
      offers: {
        "@type": "Offer",
        priceCurrency: "USD",
        price: "2500",
        priceSpecification: {
          "@type": "UnitPriceSpecification",
          minPrice: 2500,
          priceCurrency: "USD",
          unitText: "MONTH",
        },
      },
      serviceType: "Software project rescue and oversight",
    })}
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .svc { background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top right, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.04), transparent 50%), radial-gradient(ellipse at bottom left, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.03), transparent 40%), var(--bg-0); min-height: 100vh; }
  .svc-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr; gap: 64px; max-width: 1120px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--gutter); }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .svc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 24px; padding: 0 var(--gutter-sm); } }
  .svc-rail { position: sticky; top: 88px; align-self: start; height: fit-content; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-1); padding-top: 14px; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .svc-rail { position: static; display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px; padding-top: 8px; } }
  .rail-marker { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-1); letter-spacing: 0.04em; line-height: 1; }
  .rail-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-3); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; margin-top: 6px; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .rail-label { margin-top: 0; } }

  .svc-hero { padding: 80px 0 56px; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .svc-hero { padding: 48px 0 32px; } }
  .svc-epigraph { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text-3); font-style: italic; margin: 0 0 32px; padding-left: 18px; border-left: 2px solid var(--accent); max-width: 56ch; }
  .svc-h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(40px, 5.5vw, 68px); line-height: 1.04; letter-spacing: -0.025em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 28px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 20ch; }
  .svc-h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); font-weight: 700; }
  .svc-lede { font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 32px; max-width: 60ch; }
  .svc-hero-cta { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; align-items: center; margin-top: 12px; }
  .svc-btn-primary { background: var(--bg-ink); color: var(--text-on-ink); padding: 16px 28px; border-radius: 2px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: 0.02em; transition: background var(--dur-fast) var(--ease); }
  .svc-btn-primary:hover { background: #2a2724; }
  .svc-btn-ghost { color: var(--text-1); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent); padding-bottom: 2px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease); }
  .svc-btn-ghost:hover { color: var(--accent-pressed); }

  .svc-section { padding: 80px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-1); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .svc-section { padding: 48px 0; } }
  .svc-section-muted { background: var(--bg-1); }
  .svc-h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(28px, 3.5vw, 40px); line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 16px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 24ch; }
  .svc-h2 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); }
  .svc-section-lede { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 40px; max-width: 60ch; }

  .icp-card { margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .icp-card:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .icp-header { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .icp-num { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; color: var(--accent-pressed); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; background: var(--accent-subtle); padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 2px; line-height: 1; }
  .icp-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 24px); line-height: 1.25; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0; font-weight: 600; flex: 1; }
  .icp-card p { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0; max-width: 65ch; }
  .icp-card p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 500; }
  .hairline { border: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-1); margin: 32px 0 0; }

  .ledger { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-1); }
  .ledger-item { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 64px 1fr; gap: 24px; padding: 28px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .ledger-item { grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr; gap: 16px; padding: 24px 0; } }
  .ledger-num { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 24px; color: var(--accent-pressed); font-weight: 600; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .ledger-content h4 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 8px; line-height: 1.35; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.005em; }
  .ledger-content p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0; max-width: 60ch; }

  .exclude { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .exclude li { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 16px; padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border-1); color: var(--text-2); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .exclude li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .exclude-mark { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--text-4); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .exclude strong { color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
